{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/ModularArchitecture"},"abstract":[{"text":"Organize dependency injection across multiple Swift Package Manager modules.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In a modular codebase, each SPM module owns its own ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Container","type":"reference"},{"text":" subclass. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"keeps dependency boundaries clean, makes modules independently testable, and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"prevents accidental cross-module coupling."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"One-Container-per-Module","text":"One Container per Module"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each module defines exactly one container that manages all dependencies for that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"module. The container file includes the module-local typealias:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ FeatureAuth\/Sources\/AuthContainer.swift","","import Forge","import CoreProtocols","","typealias Inject<T> = ContainerInject<AuthContainer, T>","","public final class AuthContainer: Container, SharedContainer {","    public static var shared = AuthContainer()","","    public var authService: any AuthServiceProtocol {","        provide(.singleton, preview: { MockAuthService() }) {","            AuthService(network: self.networkClient)","        }","    }","","    public var networkClient: any NetworkClientProtocol {","        provide(.singleton) { URLSessionNetworkClient() }","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All "},{"code":"@Inject","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" usages within the module use the bare syntax — no container name visible:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ FeatureAuth\/Sources\/LoginViewModel.swift","","final class LoginViewModel: ObservableObject {","    @Inject(\\.authService) private var auth","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"heading","text":"Cross-Module Proxying","level":2,"anchor":"Cross-Module-Proxying"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Feature modules must not import other feature modules directly. If a module needs a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"dependency owned by another module, it "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"proxies"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" the dependency through its own"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"container:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ FeatureSearch\/Sources\/SearchContainer.swift","","import Forge","import CoreAnalytics","","public final class SearchContainer: Container, SharedContainer {","    public static var shared = SearchContainer()","","    \/\/ Proxy — delegates to another module's container","    public var analytics: any AnalyticsProtocol {","        provide { CoreAnalyticsContainer.shared.analytics }","    }","","    public var searchService: any SearchServiceProtocol {","        provide(.singleton) {","            SearchService(analytics: self.analytics)","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Benefits of Proxying","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Benefits-of-Proxying"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Test isolation"}]},{"text":" — override ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"analytics"},{"text":" on ","type":"text"},{"code":"SearchContainer","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" directly, without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"touching "},{"code":"CoreAnalyticsContainer","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Clean dependency graph","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — each module’s DI surface is fully within its own container","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Swappability","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — if ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CoreAnalytics"},{"text":" is replaced, only the proxy property needs updating","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"The-Composition-Root","text":"The Composition Root","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The app target is the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"composition root","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — the only place where all modules are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"imported and containers are wired together:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["\/\/ App\/Sources\/AppDelegate.swift","","import FeatureAuth","import FeatureSearch","import CoreAnalytics","","class AppDelegate: UIApplicationDelegate {","    func application(","        _ application: UIApplication,","        didFinishLaunchingWithOptions launchOptions: [UIApplication.LaunchOptionsKey: Any]?","    ) -> Bool {","        \/\/ Wire containers","        AuthContainer.shared = AuthContainer()","        SearchContainer.shared = SearchContainer()","        CoreAnalyticsContainer.shared = CoreAnalyticsContainer()","        return true","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Import-Dependency-Graph","text":"Import Dependency Graph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The correct architecture follows this pattern:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["CoreProtocols (protocols only — no Forge import)","       ^","       |","  Feature modules (each has its own Container)","       ^","       |","  App target (imports all modules, wires containers)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Key rules:","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Protocol modules define abstractions only — no Forge dependency needed","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Feature modules import protocol modules and Forge","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"ViewModels and services never ","type":"text"},{"code":"import","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" a concrete service module directly","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The app target is the only place that imports both protocol and concrete modules","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Best Practices","anchor":"Best-Practices"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Keep containers "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"module-scoped","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — if a container grows beyond its module’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"concerns, the module has too many responsibilities","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Make dependency properties ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"public"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — they are the module’s DI surface","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"protocol return types"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" on all dependency properties","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Proxy cross-module dependencies rather than importing other feature modules","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Forge"}],"title":"Modular Architecture"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge"]]},